School Governor,Parish Council, Farmed Goods Farm.
Lived in area 48 years-ex Scotland. {Hobbies.}Making walking sticks (sheeps and stag horns etc)Upholstery Gardening,Sheep.Great love of the countryside.Tells of poor farmers digging coal(poor quality)on Duncliffe Hill.Soldiers Field (under Duncliffe) where soldiers arrested farmworkers who were smashing machinery. One field in the area is called John Ash's leg.The story goes "The Duke of Portland,Master of hounds,lost the fox".Have you seen the fox ?"He shouted."It's ran up John Ash's leg" was the answer!"
